label: A9B5C5D2_tP42_85_c2g_cg_ag_bc-001
title: 10-4-8 [Ca$_{10}$(Pt$_{4}$As$_{8}$)(Fe$_{2}$As$_{2}$)$_{5}$] Superconductor Structure
comments:
This is a high-temperature superconducting structure from the iron-arsenide family.  The designation 10-4-8 comes from the stoichiometry of the Ca-Pt-As substitutions to the FeAs structure. 
 The data for this structure was taken at 100K. 
 The sites labled Fe actually are Fe$_{0.97}$Pt$_{0.03}$.  The Pt-I (2a) site is only partially occupied, with 12.3\% of the sites vacant. 
 There is no ICSD entry for (Ni, 2011).  We use the similar structure from (L\"{o}hnert, 2011).
